'DATA STATEMENT MAKER' TAKES ASTRING AND AN APPLESOFT LINE NUMBERAS INPUT. IT THEN CREATES A TEXTFILE NAMED 'DATA'CONSISTING OF ADATA STATEMENT WITH THE ASCII VALUESOF THE CHARACTERS IN THE STRING.IF 'DATA' ALREADY EXISTS; THEN THEDATA STATEMENT IS APPENDED TO THEEXISTING FILE. WHEN YOU'RE DONE YOUCAN EXEC THEFILE TO ADD THE DATASTATEMENTS TO AN APPLESOFT PROGRAM.